# Q&A on Responsive web Design

### **Q&A**

**Q: HTML ID meaning?**

**A: A unique identifier for manipulating a specific HTML element, declared using the 'id' attribute.**

**Q: HTML element meaning?**

**A: Individual components of an HTML document like `<p>`, `<div>`, `<a>`, forming the web page's building blocks.**

**Q: HTML attribute meaning?**

**A: Provides extra information about an HTML element, specified in the start tag in name/value pairs like name="value".**

**Q: Radio button in HTML meaning?**

**A: An input element allowing the selection of one option from a set of mutually exclusive options.**

**Note: These concepts are applied in the FreeCodeCamp's Cat App Project for hands-on experience.**
